        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 24 at 5:24PM EDT until June 24 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>SVRGRR

The National Weather Service in Grand Rapids has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northern Kalamazoo County in southwestern Michigan...

* Until 615 PM EDT.

* At 524 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Westwood, or
7 miles northwest of Kalamazoo, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Galesburg...
Parchment...           Richland...            Gull Lake...
Comstock Northwest...  Westwood...            Alamo...
Comstock...            Oshtemo...             Cooper...
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
